    {
        "content": "<p>kpshek labeled <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\">Issue #196</a></p>",
        "id": 153952558,
        "sender_full_name": "Github Notifications",
        "timestamp": 1523899765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>AlexTatiyants <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-382571267\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-382571267\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\">Issue #196</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Not requiring a complete resource for updates makes a lot of sense to me. For more complex resources (like orders), it's unlikely that the CDS service will have all of the details necessary to fully update the resource properly. The EMR is in the best position to \"merge\" changes proposed by the CDS service with the existing resource.</p>\n</blockquote>",
