        "content": "<p>kpshek assigned <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\">Issue #196</a></p>",
        "id": 154024864,
        "sender_full_name": "Github Notifications",
        "timestamp": 1544631872
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>isaacvetter <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-446649888\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-446649888\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\">Issue #196</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>From discussion with @kpshek , @brynrhodes , @brettmarquard - </p>\n<p>When FHIR PUTs or POSTs a resource, the client provides the entire resource.  We should remain consistent with FHIR. <br>\nThe consuming system could compare and only update the things that are different (and perhaps should as part of their concurrency checking).<br>\nWhen the CDS client provides an update, it should provide the entire resource. </p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 154024865,
        "sender_full_name": "Github Notifications",
        "timestamp": 1544631954
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>kpshek <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-446652514\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196#issuecomment-446652514\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/issues/196\">Issue #196</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In addition to what @isaacvetter said, we can evaluate a FHIR PATCH action in a future version of the specification.</p>\n</blockquote>",
